===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
In oracle bone script, {{Han compound|ls=psc|㳄|舟|c1=p|t2=boat}} – an overflowing river.<ref name="字源">李学勤《字源》p774</ref> This character is technically a different word than the modern {{zh-l|盜|dào|t=steal}}, used interchangeably with {{och-l|衍}} in oracle bones, or as a phonetic loan for  {{och-l|羨}}, and {{och-l|延}} in bronze script.<ref name="漢語多功能字庫">[https://humanum.arts.cuhk.edu.hk/Lexis/lexi-mf/search.php?word=盜 漢語多功能字庫 - 字頭「盜」]</ref> The component {{zh-l|*舟}} corrupted into {{zh-l|*皿}} in {{w|Chu script}}.

{{zh-l|盜|dào|t=steal}} on the other hand, is a {{Han compound|ls=ic|㳄|皿|t1=drooling; craving|t2=vessel}} – to covet someone else's possessions → to steal.

